{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:second-timothy.2",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Timothy 2 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:1",
      "text": "Thou therefore, my son, be strong in Christ Jesus:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:2",
      "text": "And the things which thou hast heard of me by many witnesses, the same commend to faithful men who shall be fit to teach others also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:3",
      "text": "Labour as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:4",
      "text": "No man, being a soldier to God, entangleth himself with secular businesses: that he may please him to whom he hath engaged himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:5",
      "text": "For he also that striveth for the mastery is not crowned, except he strive lawfully.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:6",
      "text": "The husbandman that laboureth must first partake of the fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:7",
      "text": "Understand what I say: for the Lord will give thee in all things understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:8",
      "text": "Be mindful that the Lord Jesus Christ is risen again from the dead, of the seed of David, according to my gospel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:9",
      "text": "Wherein I labour even unto bands, as an evildoer. But the word of God is not bound.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:10",
      "text": "Therefore I endure all things for the sake of the elect, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus, with heavenly glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:11",
      "text": "A faithful saying: for if we be dead with him, we shall live also with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:12",
      "text": "If we suffer, we shall also reign with him. If we deny him, he will also deny us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:13",
      "text": "If we believe not, he continueth faithful, he cannot deny himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:14",
      "text": "Of these things put them in mind, charging them before the Lord. Contend not in words: for it is to no profit, but to the subverting of the hearers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:15",
      "text": "Carefully study to present thyself approved unto God, a workman that needeth not to be ashamed, rightly handling the word of truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:16",
      "text": "But shun profane and vain babblings: for they grow much towards ungodliness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:17",
      "text": "And their speech spreadeth like a canker: of whom are Hymeneus and Philetus:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:18",
      "text": "Who have erred from the truth, saying that the resurrection is past already, and have subverted the faith of some.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:19",
      "text": "But the sure foundation of God standeth firm, having this seal: the Lord knoweth who are his; and let every one depart from iniquity who nameth the name of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:20",
      "text": "But in a great house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of earth: and some indeed unto honour, but some unto dishonour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:21",
      "text": "If any man therefore shall cleanse himself from these, he shall be a vessel unto honour, sanctified and profitable to the Lord, prepared unto every good work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:22",
      "text": "But flee thou youthful desires, and pursue justice, faith, charity and peace with them that call on the Lord out of a pure heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:23",
      "text": "And avoid foolish and unlearned questions, knowing that they beget strifes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:24",
      "text": "But the servant of the Lord must not wrangle: but be mild toward all men, apt to teach, patient,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:25",
      "text": "With modesty admonishing them that resist the truth: if peradventure God may give them repentance to know the truth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.2.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 2:26",
      "text": "And they may recover themselves from the snares of the devil by whom they are held captive at his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
